# Monotone co-batch negate (analysis sec 4.5 R9, F-A case 1).
#
# Batch 1: co-change pred row feed(1,10) AND negated key unsee(1) in ONE
#   epoch. Forward +1 (seen(1) absent-in-InI) and the `-` crossover -1
#   (copy(1,10) present-in-InNew) net to zero; both stale crossings are
#   claim-gate-dropped. out stays EMPTY.
# Batch 2: feed(2,20) with no matching unsee(2): ordinary forward path
#   publishes out(2,20). out = {(2,20)}.
# Batch 3: unsee(2): seen gains a key with a live pred row -> `-` crossover
#   retracts out(2,20). out = {} (empty).
batch
+ feed 1 10
+ unsee 1
end

batch
+ feed 2 20
end

batch
+ unsee 2
end
